snippet: The mother of Brandon Lincoln Woodard, who was killed on Monday, said detectives told her they found nothing in a search of his home.
abstract: Sandra Wellington, mother of Midtown Manhattan shooting victim Brandon Lincoln Woodard, says that detectives found no evidence of any kind in a search of his California home, and New York Police Commissioner Raymond W Kelly says investigators still have no suspects.

byline.original: By WENDY RUDERMAN and J. DAVID GOODMAN

lead_paragraph: The mother of Brandon Lincoln Woodard, who was killed on Monday, said detectives told her they found nothing in a search of his home.

headline.seo: New York Police, in California, Search Home of Midtown Shooting Victim
headline.main: Detectives ‘Found Nothing’ in Search of Shooting Victim’s California Home, Mother Says
headline.print_headline: Detectives ‘Found Nothing’ in Search of Shooting Victim’s California Home, Mother Says
